snippet.textDisplay:
I remember sending this song to her. And wrote a poem thats been pending on my notes. It goes like”

On the mountain , under the stars
I wonder how you float in the sky 
You were the breeze of my summer
The warmth of the winter
The soft star in the sky
The Ursa Major of my life
This feeling that were so seldom 
My body was quivering when I saw a glimpse of you 
Now I feel like my breath has been taken away from me 
Like the iron in my chest
The mind is full of bleeding thoughts 
The wishes we prayed upon the shooting stars 
The vow we took, part away
Left me cold like the mountain winds
I search through the garden of roses 
Where I only find thrones 
Their fragrance a memory of passions long gone
Now I have realised 
I have to relinquished the grip to the past
Im feeling, you are moving too fast 
I had look at you like the husband to his wife 
I diged a grave for myself 
Call me , find me in another dimension
A place so alienated from this world 
A place so dear to me
A garden full of roses and stars
A River near by , 
Mountains surrounded by 
Especially the snow capped mountains 
Where love gets enlightened or elated, 
no rush , no regrets, no compromises 
Solace to our souls  
Feeling you cant explain
A true content peace to our souls
    On the mountain, under the stars
